In this statement, the President acknowledges that Christians around the world are preparing to celebrate Christmas and expresses gratitude for the freedom to practice their faith. However, he also recognizes that many Christians are persecuted and forced to leave their homes due to violence and persecution. He mentions the silence of church bells in some areas of the Middle East as a tragic reminder of the atrocities committed by ISIL. The President calls for prayers for persecuted Christians and those of other faiths, as well as for the individuals working to alleviate their suffering and restore stability to their nations. He concludes by referencing a Christmas carol that speaks of the triumph of right over wrong and the hope for peace on earth.